[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]46 The First Minister[bold]&#xa0;
[normal](1) The First Minister is to be appointed by Her Majesty after nomination in accordance with section 47.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](2) The First Minister holds office at Her Majesty's pleasure.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](3) The First Minister may at any time tender resignation to Her Majesty and ceases to hold office as First Minister when it is accepted.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](4) A person ceases to hold office as the First Minister if another person is appointed to that office.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](5) The functions of the First Minister are exercisable by a person designated by the Presiding Officer if–
[normal](a) the office of the First Minister is vacant,
[normal](b) the First Minister is for any reason unable to act, or
[normal](c) the First Minister has ceased to be an Assembly member 
[normal]otherwise than by reason of a dissolution.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal](6) A person may not be designated to exercise the functions of the First Minister unless the person is–
[normal](a) an Assembly member, or
[normal](b) if the Assembly has been dissolved, a person who ceased to be an Assembly member by reason of the dissolution.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](7) A person may be designated to exercise the functions of the First Minister only on the recommendation of the Welsh Ministers (unless there is no-one holding office as a Welsh Minister appointed under section 48).
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](8) If a person is designated to exercise the functions of the First Minister, the designation continues to have effect even if the Assembly is dissolved.
