[normal]PART 6[bold]&#xa0;[bold]MISCELLANEOUS AND SUPPLEMENTARY[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]158 Interpretation[bold]&#xa0;[bold](1) In this Act (except where the context otherwise requires)–
[normal]“EU law” means–
[normal](a) all the rights, powers, liabilities, obligations and restrictions from time to time created or arising by or under the EU Treaties, and
[normal](b) all the remedies and procedures from time to time provided for by or under the EU Treaties,
[normal]“the Convention rights” has the same meaning as in the Human Rights Act 1998 (c. 42),
[normal]“cross-border body” means any body (including a government department) or undertaker exercising functions, or carrying on activities, in or with respect to 
[normal]Wales
[normal] (or any part of 
[normal]Wales
[normal]) and anywhere else,
[normal]“enactment” includes an Assembly Measure, an Act of the Assembly and subordinate
[normal] 
[normal]legislation (but see also subsection (2)),
[normal]“English border area” means a part of 
[normal]England
[normal] adjoining 
[normal]Wales
[normal] (but not the whole of
[normal] 
[normal]England
[normal]),
[normal]“financial year” means the twelve months ending with 31st March,
[normal]“function” means power or duty,
[normal]“government department” means any department of the Government of the 
[normal]United Kingdom
[normal],
[normal]“international obligations” means any international obligations of the 
[normal]United Kingdom
[normal] other than obligations to observe and implement EU law or the Convention rights,
[normal]“Minister of the Crown” 
[normal]i
[normal]ncludes the Treasury,
[normal]“modifications” includes amendments, repeals and revocations,
[normal]“subordinate legislation” has the same meaning as in the Interpretation Act 1978 (c. 30) (including an instrument made under an Assembly Measure or Act of the Assembly),
[normal]“tribunal” means any tribunal in which legal proceedings may be brought,
[normal]“
[normal]Wales
[normal]” includes the sea adjacent to 
[normal]Wales
[normal] out as far as the seaward boundary of the territorial sea, and
[normal]“Welsh zone” means the sea adjacent to 
[normal]Wales
[normal] which is—
[normal](a) within British fishery limits (that is, the limits set by or under section 1 of the
[normal] 
[normal]Fishery Limits Act 1976), and
[normal](b) specified in an Order in Council under section 58 or an order under subsection (3).
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](2) In sections 95(3), 109(2)
[normal], 116B(2)[bold] [bold]and 151(2) “enactment” includes an Act of the Scottish Parliament and an instrument made under such an Act.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](3) The Secretary of State may by order determine, or make provision for determining, for the purposes of the definitions of “Wales” and the “Welsh zone”, any boundary between waters which are to be treated as parts of the sea adjacent to Wales, or sea within British fishery limits adjacent to Wales, and those which are not.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](4) An Order in Council under section 58 may include any provision that may be included in an order under subsection (3).
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](5) No order is to be made under subsection (3) unless a draft of the statutory instrument containing it has been laid before, and approved by a resolution of, each House of Parliament.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](6) Section 13 of the National Audit Act 1983 (c. 44) (interpretation of references to the Committee of Public Accounts) applies for the purposes of this Act as for those of that Act.
